      <div rendition="class:83225 maturity:83211" type="edition" xml:lang="san-Latn">
        <!-- 
Encoded for Siddham by Eszter Somogyi, following Ramesh and Tewari's edition unless otherwise noted in comments. Version of January 2019. Comments below by Dániel Balogh are offered "as is" and do not represent a thoroughly researched or considered opinion. 
-->
        <p><lb n="1"/>valkhāḥ parama-bhaṭṭāraka-pādānuddhyāto mahārāja-bhuluṇḍaḥ samājñāpayati sarvvān evāsma<!-- 
L1 RT: bhuluṇḍah 
--><lb break="no" n="2"/>
t-santakān āyuktakān
</p>
        <p>vijñātam astu vaḥ samanujānīmo <supplied reason="subaudible">’</supplied>sya valkhā<supplied reason="omitted">yā</supplied>m eva bhojikā-bhaṭṭa-bandhulā<!-- 
L2. Retaining RT's emendation valkhāyām, but once we emend, perhaps sya should also be emended to syāṁ. 
--><lb break="no" n="3"/>-pratiṣṭhāpitaka-bappapiśācadevasya ūrikā-rāṣṭre pūrvva-bhujyamānakaṁ bhojikā-bhaṭṭa-bandhu<lb break="no" n="4"/>
lā-vijñāpyād devāgrāhārakaṁ nāma gavayapānīyakaṁ caivam etad grāma-dvayam api devāgrā<lb break="no" n="5"/>
hāra-nyāyena devasya bali-caru-satra-dhūpa-gandha-puṣpa-mālyopayojyaṁ A-cāṭa-bhaṭa-prā<!-- 
L5. RT: hārā-nyāyena. I'd expect hāra, and do not see an ā mātrā in the rubbing. 
--><lb break="no" n="6"/>
veśyam ācandrā<sic>rk</sic>a-tārakā-kālīnam evam idānīm asyāsmābhiḥ kr̥tānujñātaṁ pāśupata-deva<!-- 
L6 RT: kr̥tanujñātaṁ 
--><lb break="no" n="7"/>-prasādak<choice>
            <sic>a</sic>
            <corr>ā</corr>
          </choice>dyānām ucitayā devāgrāhāra-bhuktyā bhuñjatāṁ kr̥ṣatāṁ ca sarvvair evāsmat-pa<lb break="no" n="8"/>
kṣa tat-kulyādibhis <choice>
            <sic>
              <unclear>satamuvanu</unclear>
            </sic>
            <corr>samanumantavyaṁ</corr>
          </choice></p>
        <p>gomika dūtaka<!-- 
L8 I keep RT's reading satamuvanu. The rubbing is illegible. RT hypothesise that "The original writing in ink must have contained the usual word samanumantavyam," which would have been rubbed off inadvertently, leaving the engraver at a loss. 
--></p>
        <p>varṣe <num value="54"><g type="numeral">50</g> 4</num><supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> <choice>
            <sic>bhaṁgavaṣiṣṭe </sic>
            <corr>bhagavac-chiṣṭaiḥ</corr>
          </choice> adhiṣṭhitaṁ<!-- 
L8, RT: bhangavaṣiṣṭe. 
--></p>
        <ab><lb n="01"/>vaiś<choice>
            <sic>a</sic>
            <corr>ā</corr>
          </choice>kha śu <num value="4">4</num><supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> mahārāja-bhuluṇḍasya<!-- 
L margin.1 is engraved on the left margin, bottom to top, characters rotated 90° couterclockweise.. 
